271 /**
272 We support a number of predefined keys, such as "error-code" or
273 "message". These are defined here. We also support user-defined
274 "ad hoc" (or "generic") keys that let users of the error stack
275 add values with arbitrary keys (as long as those keys don't coincide
276 with the wellknown ones, anyway).
277
278 The idea here is that we want the flexibility of arbitrary keys,
279 while being able to do certain optimizations for the common case.
280 This also allows us to relatively cheaply add some convenience
281 features, e.g. we know that error symbol ("ER_STARTUP") and
282 error code (1451) are related, and can supply one as the other
283 is submitted. Likewise of course, we can use the error code to
284 fetch the associated registered error message string for that
285 error code. Et cetera!
286 */
